  "text": "Experiment 1 was conducted to confirm that H.C., like individuals with adult-onset amnesia [CITATION_1] , would benefit from spaced presentations of items in a simple word-list learning task. In the list-learning task, RI was carefully controlled, such that it was similar across four lag conditions. These parameters were chosen to stay true to the paradigm used by Cermak and colleagues while eliminating the potential confound of unequal RI between lags.",
